# Day 3: Media Elements in HTML5

This project demonstrates how to use HTML5 media elements, such as `<audio>` and `<video>`, to add multimedia content to your webpage. It also includes an example of embedding external content like YouTube videos.

## Features
- Audio playback using the `<audio>` tag.
- Video playback with the `<video>` tag and fallback content for unsupported browsers.
- Embedding content from external sources using `<iframe>`.

## Instructions
1. Clone the repository.
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/sajan69/CodeFrontier
   cd day 3
   ```
2. Open `multimedia.html` in your browser to view the example.

## Files
- `multimedia.html`: The main HTML file containing examples of media elements.
- Placeholder media files (`sample-audio.mp3`, `sample-video.mp4`, `video-poster.jpg`) can be replaced with actual content for testing.

